editorialNotes.standard: Let kids loose in a construction zone where they can place a roof, lay a foundation, paint a house, and more. Children will feel like one of the builders as they operate a crane, cement mixer, and excavator, and theyâll delight in all the surprising little interactions with workers in and around the job sites.

This charming bedtime story will soothe your young child with delightful imagery and a simple but engaging spoken tale. Inside an exquisitely illustrated farmhouse, adorable woodland animals need help turning out the lights to fall asleep. Intuitive controls and fun interactive surprises make Nighty Night a pleasure to explore, and with optional narration, you and your toddler can settle in to be entertained or bring your own imaginations to the wonderful nighttime world.

editorialNotes.standard: Fox and Sheepâs endearing app gives kids the power to healâand helps parents encourage kindness and curiosity. Through trial and error, little ones figure out how to treat a sniffly owl, a sunburned rabbit, and other beautifully animated patients. Sometimes they need bandages and medicine; sometimes a healthy snack will do the trick. Animalsâ flashbacks and reactions offer important clues in the delightful quest to make them smile again.

An utterly charming way to introduce young kids to music and animation, Loopimal is simple and powerful in a way that almost defies description. Kids arrange and rearrange tiles in sequences underneath a cute polar bear, octopus, and the like, triggering a series of musical tones mirrored by adorable dances from the animal gang. There are no goals and no consequencesâjust a safe place to learn, play, and laugh.
